What you need to know:

Rahimi, 24, a wide attacker from famed Casablanca outfit Raja Athletic Club, has wreaked havoc at the tournament for home-based players, scoring a chart-topping five goals in five matchesAfter a show start, in which they scored only once against Togo and were held goalless by Rwanda, Rahimi and his fellow Atlas Lions have been irresistible, netting 12 times in three matchesWhile Morocco have been outstanding as an attacking force, Mali have been equally impressive in preventing opponents from scoring, conceding only once in five matches